        In 1999, there is       
 a third indictment for Rafael. 

383
00:21:31,524 --> 00:21:34,025
     This time, he is caught    
     lying on an application    

384
00:21:34,027 --> 00:21:36,444
  for a permit to catch squid,  

385
00:21:36,446 --> 00:21:39,747
     saying he has a history    
        in the business.        

386
00:21:39,749 --> 00:21:42,199
     Mullett: The government    
 followed up on that paperwork, 

387
00:21:42,201 --> 00:21:44,401
and they found that these people

388
00:21:44,403 --> 00:21:46,871
    had never purchased squid   
          from Carlos.          

389
00:21:46,873 --> 00:21:48,422
   One of the businesses said,  

390
00:21:48,424 --> 00:21:50,291
   "I wasn't even in business   

391
00:21:50,293 --> 00:21:55,262
  at the time that he allegedly 
       sold me the squid."      

392
00:21:55,264 --> 00:21:58,632
      Narrator: Rafael has      
      no defense this time.     

393
00:21:58,634 --> 00:22:02,252
 He pleads guilty to five counts
      of false statements,      

394
00:22:02,254 --> 00:22:05,923
  and is sentenced to probation 
  and six months' house arrest. 

395
00:22:05,925 --> 00:22:10,227
  And when the punishment ends, 
 it's back to business as usual.

396
00:22:10,229 --> 00:22:16,400
     And his fines mount --     
  $25,000 here, $30,000 there.  

397
00:22:16,402 --> 00:22:18,268
    Those monetary penalties    
        probably would've       

398
00:22:18,270 --> 00:22:21,605
    put the average fisherman   
        out of business.        

399
00:22:21,607 --> 00:22:24,909
    Narrator: But Rafael can    
        afford the fines.       

400
00:22:24,911 --> 00:22:29,463
At the time, he says he is worth
      at least $10 million.     

401
00:22:29,465 --> 00:22:34,418
        And that is when        
     The Codfather is born.     

402
00:22:34,420 --> 00:22:39,473
   Bullard: He called himself   
        "The Codfather."        

403
00:22:39,475 --> 00:22:46,347
     So, he modeled himself     
      over a crime family.      

404
00:22:46,349 --> 00:22:50,634
        He wasn't ashamed       
     of being a lawbreaker.     

405
00:22:50,636 --> 00:22:54,739
      He bragged about it.      

406
00:22:54,741 --> 00:22:57,808
   Narrator: And while Rafael   
   continually thumbs his nose  

407
00:22:57,810 --> 00:22:59,443
       at law enforcement,      

408
00:22:59,445 --> 00:23:03,781
    most other fishermen make   
  a different, painful choice.  

409
00:23:03,783 --> 00:23:06,150
        Sykes: None of us       
      like the regulations,     

410
00:23:06,152 --> 00:23:08,485
      but they're not just      
         for some people        

411
00:23:08,487 --> 00:23:10,171
    and not others, you know,   

412
00:23:10,173 --> 00:23:16,460
