462
00:28:43,756 --> 00:28:45,606
     Quintessential Carlos.     

463
00:28:45,608 --> 00:28:48,642
  "I'll squash him like a bug." 

464
00:28:48,644 --> 00:28:51,712
    Shelley: He would get up    
       at the mic and say,      

465
00:28:51,714 --> 00:28:56,216
      "I don't give a damn      
   about you small fishermen.   

466
00:28:56,218 --> 00:28:58,118
     I'm gonna get it all."     

467
00:28:58,120 --> 00:29:04,742
       I mean, it was not       
     a veiled state of mind.    

468
00:29:04,744 --> 00:29:07,294
  Narrator: And then, in 2010,  

469
00:29:07,296 --> 00:29:10,781
       a new set of rules       
 is put in place for groundfish 

470
00:29:10,783 --> 00:29:13,917
     that gives him the edge    
       he is looking for.       

471
00:29:13,919 --> 00:29:18,622
    For many, the days-at-sea   
       regulation is gone.      

472
00:29:18,624 --> 00:29:20,758
    Now government scientists   
         will determine         

473
00:29:20,760 --> 00:29:24,595
  how many fish of each species 
    can be caught in a year,    

474
00:29:24,597 --> 00:29:27,931
and each fisherman will be given
 a percentage of that number -- 

475
00:29:27,933 --> 00:29:32,469
  a quota for how many they can 
   catch of each kind of fish.  

476
00:29:32,471 --> 00:29:36,740
   And then the boat can pick   
  and choose when it goes out,  

477
00:29:36,742 --> 00:29:38,475
    how many days it goes out   

478
00:29:38,477 --> 00:29:42,696
     to catch its allotment     
          for the year.         

479
00:29:42,698 --> 00:29:44,648
  Narrator: It's made to order  
       for Carlos Rafael,       

480
00:29:44,650 --> 00:29:47,651
     because the percentage     
 a fisherman gets of a species, 

481
00:29:47,653 --> 00:29:51,455
     like cod, for example,     
    is based on how many cod    

482
00:29:51,457 --> 00:29:54,708
       a fisherman caught       
        in recent years.        

483
00:29:54,710 --> 00:29:57,878
   Shelley: So the people who   
       fished the hardest       

484
00:29:57,880 --> 00:30:01,298
    on the most-stressed fish   
           were given           

485
00:30:01,300 --> 00:30:07,971
    the biggest percentage of   
 the future quota on that fish. 

486
00:30:07,973 --> 00:30:11,859
Narrator: And so, Rafael is able
   to obtain around 50 permits  

487
00:30:11,861 --> 00:30:15,512
        to catch millions       
       of pounds of fish.       

488
00:30:15,514 --> 00:30:18,115
            Lelling:            
  These quotas, these permits,  

489
00:30:18,117 --> 00:30:21,735
      were the lifeblood of     
 commercial fishing after 2010. 

490
00:30:21,737 --> 00:30:24,371
  If you had a lot of permits,  
 you could do a lot of fishing, 

491
00:30:24,373 --> 00:30:25,656
 you could make a lot of money. 

492
00:30:25,658 --> 00:30:27,407
       If you didn't have       
        a lot of permits,       

493
00:30:27,409 --> 00:30:30,744
  then you couldn't do a lot of 
fishing and make a lot of money.

494
00:30:30,746 --> 00:30:32,212
   Narrator: It sounds simple,  

495
00:30:32,214 --> 00:30:35,699
       but it is not when       
     it comes to groundfish,    

496
00:30:35,701 --> 00:30:39,002
       and that is because      
    groundfish swim together.   

497
00:30:39,004 --> 00:30:40,754
   And when the nets go down,   

498
00:30:40,756 --> 00:30:44,391
        different species       
      get caught together.      

499
00:30:44,393 --> 00:30:48,345
   Lelling: So, whatever fish   
      is the lowest quota,      

500
00:30:48,347 --> 00:30:50,714
   once you caught your quota   
          of that fish,         

501
00:30:50,716 --> 00:30:52,516
    you had to stop fishing.    

502
00:30:52,518 --> 00:30:56,052
So, if you caught all the yellow
 tail you were allowed to catch,

