582
00:37:18,320 --> 00:37:21,321
 in fines for civil violations. 

583
00:37:21,323 --> 00:37:23,773
        You can cite him        
    for doing this and that,    

584
00:37:23,775 --> 00:37:26,660
           and for him          
   it's like a parking ticket.  

585
00:37:26,662 --> 00:37:29,496
   Something more was needed.   

586
00:37:29,498 --> 00:37:33,283
    Narrator: And the chance    
     to do "something more"     

587
00:37:33,285 --> 00:37:35,985
     comes in January 2015,     

588
00:37:35,987 --> 00:37:38,821
 when IRS agents see an article 
    in the New Bedford paper    

589
00:37:38,823 --> 00:37:43,009
       saying that Rafael       
   wants to sell his business.  

590
00:37:43,011 --> 00:37:48,848
     He tells the reporter,     
 "I'm gonna cash in and screw." 

591
00:37:48,850 --> 00:37:52,218
     So, I saw that article     
          and thought,          

592
00:37:52,220 --> 00:37:54,287
      "If he wants to sell      
          his business,         

593
00:37:54,289 --> 00:37:57,123
     maybe we're interested     
         in buying it."         

594
00:37:57,125 --> 00:38:03,863
Narrator: And so, IRS undercover
 agents place a call to Rafael. 

595
00:38:03,865 --> 00:38:06,566
  They just picked up the phone 
    and called him and said,    

596
00:38:06,568 --> 00:38:08,034
     "We're a bunch of guys     
         from New York.         

597
00:38:08,036 --> 00:38:09,736
      We're thinking about      
      buying your business.     

598
00:38:09,738 --> 00:38:11,571
  Would you sit down with us?"  

599
00:38:11,573 --> 00:38:17,494
 Narrator: Rafael takes the bait
and agrees to a meeting in June.

600
00:38:17,496 --> 00:38:21,381
   There are three undercover   
  agents working the operation. 

601
00:38:21,383 --> 00:38:24,551
     One is playing the part    
     of a financial broker.     

602
00:38:24,553 --> 00:38:27,053
 The other two are his clients, 

603
00:38:27,055 --> 00:38:30,006
         who claim to be        
       Russian investors.       

604
00:38:30,008 --> 00:38:33,259
 They meet Rafael at his office.

605
00:38:33,261 --> 00:38:36,696
     He wasn't anybody like     
       I ever met before.       

606
00:38:36,698 --> 00:38:39,165
  Narrator: Because the agents  
        work undercover,        

607
00:38:39,167 --> 00:38:42,669
         they asked that        
    their faces be concealed.   

608
00:38:42,671 --> 00:38:43,937
      Alex: If you give him     
         an opportunity,        

609
00:38:43,939 --> 00:38:46,172
    he'll talk about himself    
           constantly.          

610
00:38:46,174 --> 00:38:50,110
     Gary: Larger than life.    
       Very in your face.       

611
00:38:50,112 --> 00:38:54,397
  Lots of vulgarity, swearing,  
       yelling, screaming.      

612
00:38:54,399 --> 00:38:57,951
      I didn't realize that     
   the "F" word could be used   

613
00:38:57,953 --> 00:39:02,389
 in so many ways in a sentence, 
       to be quite frank.       

614
00:39:02,391 --> 00:39:05,358
     Narrator: The Russians'    
   first question to Rafael --  

615
00:39:05,360 --> 00:39:07,327
        What does he want       
        for his business?       

616
00:39:07,329 --> 00:39:12,432
   His answer -- $175 million.  

617
00:39:12,434 --> 00:39:15,918
            Lelling:            
  And they said to him, "Well,  
  we'd have to see your books." 

618
00:39:15,920 --> 00:39:19,389
   So, when Carlos showed them  
      his legitimate books,     

619
00:39:19,391 --> 00:39:22,392
 it did not support that price. 

620
00:39:22,394 --> 00:39:24,644
      So they said to him,      

621
00:39:24,646 --> 00:39:30,066
      "Why would we pay you     
$175 million for this business?"

622
00:39:30,068 --> 00:39:32,435
            Narrator:           
  And to answer that question,  

623
00:39:32,437 --> 00:39:34,738
he needs to reveal his scheme --

624
00:39:34,740 --> 00:39:38,742
   how he gets around the law,  
   and keeps his profits high.  

625
00:39:52,974 --> 00:39:57,627
     So that is his secret.     
       It's called lying.       

626
00:39:57,629 --> 00:39:59,629
      This is what he does.     

627
00:39:59,631 --> 00:40:02,515
      If a captain catches      
      3,000 pounds of cod,      

628
00:40:02,517 --> 00:40:05,769
    which is a fish for which   
   Rafael has a low allotment,  

629
00:40:05,771 --> 00:40:09,472
he calls the cod something else,
          like haddock,         

630
00:40:09,474 --> 00:40:12,609
        a fish for which        
    he has a huge allotment.    

631
00:40:20,485 --> 00:40:22,151
    It's just a simple matter   

632
00:40:22,153 --> 00:40:26,489
 of falsifying official reports 
     that are sent to NOAA.     

633
00:40:26,491 --> 00:40:28,208
 Rafael tells the boat captains 

634
00:40:28,210 --> 00:40:31,010
        how to lie about        
        what they catch.        

635
00:40:31,012 --> 00:40:33,963
   He lies about what he buys.  

636
00:40:33,965 --> 00:40:36,766
   Lelling: So, back at NOAA,   
   when they compare the two,   

637
00:40:36,768 --> 00:40:40,804
  they don't detect any fraud,  
       because they match.      

638
00:40:40,806 --> 00:40:43,973
    Narrator: And so, Rafael    
   can catch whatever he wants  

639
00:40:43,975 --> 00:40:46,392
and not be limited by his quota,

640
00:40:46,394 --> 00:40:49,178
       what the government      
      allows him to catch.      

641
00:40:49,180 --> 00:40:51,815
   When law-abiding fishermen   
          reach the end         

642
00:40:51,817 --> 00:40:54,317
    of their allowable share    
          of the catch,         

643
00:40:54,319 --> 00:40:56,653
they are forced to stop fishing,

644
00:40:56,655 --> 00:41:01,491
     or they have the option    
       to buy more quota.       

645
00:41:01,493 --> 00:41:05,879
     They gave me, I think,     
 6,000 pounds of winter flounder

646
00:41:05,881 --> 00:41:10,884
       for the whole year,      
      which starts May 1st.     

647
00:41:10,886 --> 00:41:12,702
 So, I've already used that up. 

648
00:41:12,704 --> 00:41:15,338
          So, in order          
      to stay in business,      

649
00:41:15,340 --> 00:41:21,043
   I have to lease the rights   
     to catch more flounder     

650
00:41:21,045 --> 00:41:24,714
     from another fisherman.    

651
00:41:24,716 --> 00:41:26,850
   Narrator: Honest fishermen,  
       like Rodman Sykes,       

652
00:41:26,852 --> 00:41:31,187
 are forced to pay for the right
       to catch more fish.      

653
00:41:31,189 --> 00:41:33,356
       Because he is lying      
       to the government,       

654
00:41:33,358 --> 00:41:37,327
     Carlos Rafael does not     
       have that expense.       

655
00:41:51,126 --> 00:41:56,746
 And Rafael claims his captains 
profit from the scheme, as well,

656
00:41:56,748 --> 00:41:59,799
    because he requires them    
     to chip in on any quota    

657
00:41:59,801 --> 00:42:02,735
    that he is forced to buy.   

658
00:42:15,317 --> 00:42:19,402
   And later, when the scheme   
         is discovered,         

659
00:42:19,404 --> 00:42:24,157
  some people on the waterfront 
 understand a captain's choice. 

660
00:42:24,159 --> 00:42:26,910
            Kendall:            
   I can tell you one thing --  

661
00:42:26,912 --> 00:42:31,998
       If you're a captain      
     of a fairly good vessel    

662
00:42:32,000 --> 00:42:34,283
 that's making fairly good money

663
00:42:34,285 --> 00:42:37,453
         at a time where        
    some of your compatriots    

664
00:42:37,455 --> 00:42:39,672
      are starving to death     
    or going out of business    

665
00:42:39,674 --> 00:42:41,624
     or losing their homes,     

666
00:42:41,626 --> 00:42:44,310
      you'll pretty much do     
