00:58:03,981 --> 00:58:06,365
    Narrator: In March 2017,    

885
00:58:06,367 --> 00:58:08,784
       faced with 15 hours      
    of undercover recordings    

886
00:58:08,786 --> 00:58:10,819
     made by the IRS agents,    

887
00:58:10,821 --> 00:58:13,622
      Rafael pleads guilty      
         to conspiracy,         

888
00:58:13,624 --> 00:58:15,457
   falsifying federal records,  

889
00:58:15,459 --> 00:58:20,012
      bulk-cash smuggling,      
        and tax evasion.        

890
00:58:20,014 --> 00:58:21,380
      Through his attorney,     

891
00:58:21,382 --> 00:58:23,448
           he declines          
   "American Greed's" request   

892
00:58:23,450 --> 00:58:26,718
 to participate in this report. 

893
00:58:26,720 --> 00:58:29,888
   At his sentencing hearing,   
       Rafael argues that,      

894
00:58:29,890 --> 00:58:32,124
   in perpetrating his scheme,  

895
00:58:32,126 --> 00:58:35,894
 he was actually trying to help 
   fishermen in New Bedford --  

896
00:58:35,896 --> 00:58:38,197
 He wanted to keep them working.

897
00:58:38,199 --> 00:58:42,134
      He asks for 24 months     
   of "community confinement,"  

898
00:58:42,136 --> 00:58:45,904
     claiming that his crime    
     was stupid, not greedy.    

899
00:58:45,906 --> 00:58:49,341
  The judge disagrees, saying,  
      "This was not stupid.     

900
00:58:49,343 --> 00:58:51,176
       This was corrupt."       

901
00:58:51,178 --> 00:58:56,031
       He sentences Rafael      
     to 46 months in prison.    

902
00:58:56,033 --> 00:58:59,718
I think he was convinced to give
  Carlos Rafael a high sentence 

903
00:58:59,720 --> 00:59:04,923
       by the sheer extent      
